SKILL|notion|"Notion API + ntn CLI: pages, databases, markdown, Workers."
STEP|1|Create an integration at https://notion.so/my-integrations
STEP|2|Copy the API key (starts with `ntn_` or `secret_`)
STEP|3|Store in `~/.hermes/.env`:
STEP|4|**Share target pages/databases with the integration** in Notion: page menu `...` → `Connect to` → your integration name. Without this, the API returns 404 for that page even though it exists.
STEP|5|Skip `ntn login` — use the integration token instead.** This works headlessly, no browser needed:
STEP|6|`key=value` — string fields
STEP|7|`key[nested]=value` — nested object fields
STEP|8|`key:=value` — typed assignment (booleans, numbers, null, arrays)
STEP|9|Q3 roadmap
STEP|10|Hiring"
STEP|11|**Title:** `{"title": [{"text": {"content": "..."}}]}`
STEP|12|**Rich text:** `{"rich_text": [{"text": {"content": "..."}}]}`
STEP|13|**Select:** `{"select": {"name": "Option"}}`
STEP|14|**Multi-select:** `{"multi_select": [{"name": "A"}, {"name": "B"}]}`
STEP|15|**Date:** `{"date": {"start": "2026-01-15", "end": "2026-01-16"}}`
STEP|16|**Checkbox:** `{"checkbox": true}`
STEP|17|**Number:** `{"number": 42}`
STEP|18|**URL:** `{"url": "https://..."}`
STEP|19|**Email:** `{"email": "user@example.com"}`
STEP|20|**Relation:** `{"relation": [{"id": "page_id"}]}`
STEP|21|**Databases became data sources.** Use `/data_sources/` endpoints for queries and retrieval.
STEP|22|**Two IDs per database:** `database_id` and `data_source_id`.
STEP|23|Search returns databases as `"object": "data_source"` with the `data_source_id` field.
STEP|24|**Syncs** — pull data from external APIs into a Notion database on a schedule (default 30 min).
STEP|25|**Tools** — appear as callable tools inside Notion's Custom Agents.
STEP|26|**Webhooks** — receive HTTP events from external services (GitHub, Stripe, etc.) and act in Notion.
STEP|27|Plan / platform gating:**
STEP|28|CLI works on all plans. **Deploying Workers requires Business or Enterprise.**
STEP|29|`ntn` is macOS/Linux only as of May 2026. Windows users need WSL2 or to wait for native support.
STEP|30|Free through August 11, 2026; metered on Notion credits after.
STEP|31|Blocks beyond CommonMark:**
STEP|32|Inline:**
STEP|33|Mentions: `<mention-user url="..."/>`, `<mention-page url="...">Title</mention-page>`, `<mention-date start="2026-05-15"/>`
STEP|34|Underline: `<span underline="true">text</span>`
STEP|35|Color: `<span color="blue">text</span>` or block-level `{color="blue"}` on the first line
STEP|36|Math: inline `$x^2$`, block `$$ ... $$`
STEP|37|Citations: `[^https://example.com]`
STEP|38|Colors:** `gray brown orange yellow green blue purple pink red`, plus `*_bg` variants for backgrounds.
STEP|39|Page/database IDs are UUIDs (with or without dashes — both accepted).
STEP|40|Rate limit: ~3 requests/second average. The CLI doesn't bypass this.
STEP|41|The API cannot set database **view** filters — that's UI-only.
STEP|42|Use `"is_inline": true` when creating data sources to embed them in a page.
STEP|43|Always pass `-s` to curl to suppress progress bars (cleaner agent output).
STEP|44|Pipe JSON through `jq` when reading: `... \| jq '.results[0].properties'`.
STEP|45|Notion also ships an MCP server now (`Notion MCP`, ~91% more token-efficient on DB ops than the previous version) — wire it via Hermes' MCP support if you want streaming Notion access from inside a se
